==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Neologism
<hw>Ne*ol"o*gism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>n⟦eacute⟧ologisme</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The introduction
of new words, or the use of old words in a new sense.</def> <rj><au>Mrs.
Browning.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A new word, phrase, or expression.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A new doctrine; specifically, rationalism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Neologist</ent>⟦br⟧
